OL,3,CAnjem Choudary 'ran risk of causing
OL,4,Cdeaths of many people' by directing
OL,5,Cterror
OL,7,FThe court heard that Choudary, whose
OL,8,Flicence conditions expired in July
OL,9,F2021 following his 2018 release from
OL,10,Fprison, said he viewed being called an
OL,11,Fextremist or fanatic as a "medallion"
OL,12,Fduring lectures.
OL,14,FKhaled Hussein, 29, from Canada, who
OL,15,Fprosecutors said was a "follower and
OL,16,Fdedicated supporter" of Choudary, was
OL,17,Ffound guilty of membership of ALM.
OL,19,FHe was jailed for five years with an
OL,20,Fextra year on licence.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G14/17
